Package bytecodeparser.analysis.stack

Class Summary
Array A StackElement that stands for an array.
Constant<T> A StackElement that is a constant.
Constant.DoubleConstant A StackElement that stands for a Double Constant.
Constant.FloatConstant A StackElement that stands for a Float Constant.
Constant.IntegerConstant A StackElement that stands for an Integer Constant.
Constant.LongConstant A StackElement that stands for a Long Constant.
Constant.StringConstant A StackElement that stands for a String Constant.
Constant.WhateverConstant A StackElement that stands for an Object Constant (so, whatever constant...).
Stack Represents the current stack's state.
StackAnalyzer A class to analyze a behavior.
StackAnalyzer.Frame A bytecode frame.
StackAnalyzer.Frames An collection of Frame, allowing to iterate over the frames and insert some bytecode if needed.
StackElement A Stack Element.
TOP A StackElement that is a part of a two-words Element.
TrackableArray A trackable Array is an array of known elements at compile time: its content can be "guessed" by the analyzer.
ValueFromLocalVariable A StackElement representing a value that was read from a localVariable (so the value may be known at this time).
VoidElement  
Whatever A StackElement of something we don't know anything about at compile-time.
